# Rasm Bridge Scenarios

Read `.claude/skills/testing-cs/SKILL.md`, `tools/rhino-bridge/README.md`, `tools/rhino-bridge/AGENTS.md`, and nearest test `AGENTS.md`.

## Shape

- Path scenarios under `tests/csharp/libs/<Project>/<MirrorPath>/scenarios/*.verify.csx`.
- Keep scripts source-only: no `#r`, no `#load`, no absolute paths.
- Group related runtime checks per file because each Rhino handshake costs several seconds.
- Use only public product assemblies and staged `Rasm.TestKit.Scenarios` capsules.

## Evidence

- Author scenarios with `Scenario.Run("theme", CAPTURE_PATH, (key, facts) => { ... });`.
- Add facts with `facts.Add(string key, object value);`.
- Prefer structured booleans, counts, names, tolerances, and file references over narrative console text.
- Use `Capture` only for visual or document evidence that static tests cannot prove.

## Prohibited

- Do not call `BridgeMarker.EmitFact`, `BridgeMarker.EmitScenarioHeader`, or per-fact `Console.WriteLine("key=value")`.
- Do not manually stage references or load assemblies inside the scenario.
- Do not automate Rhino settings or templates from scenarios.

## Validation

Run `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` for runtime behavior. Keep managed assertions in `*.spec.cs`.
